“We want to engage members from both parties in the legislative process, to get our democracy working again the way it was designed.” -@SenateMajLdr in 2014.

“The greatest way to ensure stability in our laws is to ensure that everyone has an opportunity to participate in some way in the passage.” Is this no longer true, @SenateMajLdr? These are your words.

.@SenateMajLdr again in 2014: “There is a desire to get this institution back to the way it used to function, which honors & respects all the members & allows everybody to participate & offer their ideas, regardless of party."

.@SenateMajLdr in 2014: “bills should come to the floor, be thoroughly debated, and include a robust amendment process.” Partisan ram jobs this year: health care, TrumpTax bill, budget. Yet in 2017 zero Democratic amendment votes outside the sham budget process.
When you control the institutions, you must govern. Democrats are trying to make it easy for you. Let’s do our job and get these bipartisan priorities done.
And let’s agree to raise the caps equally on defense and non-defense spending so we can write bipartisan appropriations bills.
Let’s provide relief to western states devastated by wildfire. That’s bipartisan.
Let’s get disaster assistance to Texas, Florida, Puerto Rico, and the US Virgin Islands, and coastal resilience. That’s bipartisan.
Let’s protect the Dreamers from the threat of deportation by passing the DREAM Act. That’s bipartisan.
Let’s give our veterans the care they deserve. That’s bipartisan.
Let’s help community health centers keep their doors open. That’s bipartisan.
Let’s restore CHIP, so poor children can get basic health care. That’s bipartisan.
Let’s give states, health providers, and law enforcement the resources to fight the opioid epidemic. That’s bipartisan.
Let’s secure the border and stop the flow of drugs. That’s bipartisan.
